                        <provenance>                       
                            The provenance of the manuscript is unknown. At a certain time, the manuscript belonged to <persName ref="PRS13179Gabra" role="owner"><roleName type="title">ʾAbbā</roleName> Gabra Giyorgis</persName> from <placeName ref="LOC3199Galaba">Galabbadā</placeName>.
                            According to the account on the manuscripts’ provenance given by Tisserant, this manuscript was added to the collection of the Sacra Congregatio de Propaganda 
                            Fide between 1838 and 1856, possibly before 1845 (the year in which <persName ref="PRS13179Gabra" role="owner"/> died).
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition when="1902">The manuscript entered the Vatican library in 1902, during the pontificate of <persName ref="PRS6258LeoXIII"/> (<date>1878–1903</date>).</acquisition>
